definitions.definition: Total income or cash flow minus expenditures . The money or other benefit a non-governmental organization or individual receives in exchange for products and services sold at an advertised price.

examples: Reading such an enlightening book on the subject was of much profit to his studies.

main_definition: ( accounting , economics ) Total income or cash flow minus expenditures . The money or other benefit a non-governmental organization or individual receives in exchange for products and services sold at an advertised price.
secondary_definitions: ( dated , literary ) Benefit, positive result obtained.
( property law ) Ellipsis of profit à prendre .
